  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the \"Voice2Literacy\" App**\n\nI\'m focusing on defining the scope of \"Voice2Literacy.\" The instructions highlight the need for a literacy coach application specifically tailored for 4th-grade students. I\'m currently interpreting the user\'s requirements and identifying the core functionalities this application must possess to meet their literacy goals.\n\n\n**Clarifying the Application Build**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to the actual application build. The user has provided a \"build profile\" that includes system architecture for a chatbot, interaction scaffolding, and a teacher dashboard data schema, implying a full-stack or client-side application using an LLM. The core function is clear: receive audio, celebrate effort, and guide iterative improvement. This could leverage Web Speech API or the Gemini API for speech recognition and/or text-to-speech.\n\n\n**Assessing App Permissions & Skills**\n\nI\'m now deep-diving into the app\'s technical capabilities. Since it\'s in an iframe, I\'m checking available permissions; I see we can request the microphone! I\'m reviewing the required skills, and `firebase-integration` is a strong fit for storing teacher dashboard session logs (`raw_input`, `edited_version`, etc.). `gemini-api` is also key; the application *needs* AI as the \"Voice2Literacy\" coach. I\'m excited to use Gemini for guidance and edits. I\'m also considering `oauth-integration`, even though it wasn\'t specified. Time for a skill check!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now inspect the Firebase integration skill documentation to ensure our database architecture aligns with best practices for logging student sessions and teacher dashboards."
