  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the teacher dashboard\'s implementation. My priority is a visually appealing, administrative design, leveraging slate and indigo color accents. I\'ve begun to consider the dashboard\'s structure, aiming for clear sections. The first section I\'m considering will be an analytics summary grid, focusing on key data points like completed sessions, average engagement, and skill focus.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create `/src/components/TeacherDashboard.tsx`, an administrative console for educators. It will display:\n1. An Analytics Summary Grid displaying key metrics (total logs, average engagement score, and a skill mastery breakdown).\n2. A Class Roster highlighting each student\'s current working/mastered skills, session counts, and most recent badge.\n3. Detailed Session Logs displaying a side-by-side diff (raw spoken text vs. polished edited version) and teacher-facing annotations (`skill_mastery_focus`, `sub_skill`, `engagement_score`, and detailed `coach_notes`).\n4. Search and filters to easily sort session history by student name or skill focus.\n5. An interactive Lesson Customizer where teachers can manage target \"Juicy Words\" lists and set focus tracks."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 418192407
    }
