    thinking: "**Analyzing StudentCoach.tsx**\n\nI\'m now diving into `src/components/StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'m starting by reviewing its structure, specifically focusing on the Container div. My initial goal is to identify potential style changes and improvements for this component. I plan to document what I find.\n\n\n**Revising Container Styles**\n\nI\'ve significantly updated the container\'s aesthetic. The `StudentCoach.tsx` now has a clean white background, a refined border color (`#e5e1d5`), and improved, high-quality curves via a radius of `32px`. The shadow has also been changed to `shadow-sm`, and I\'ve replaced the border style with a border class.\n\n\n**Incorporating Natural Tones**\n\nI\'m now integrating our natural tones design elements into the header. I\'ve focused on the `student-header` div, applying a border color and subtle color palette. The book icon and text elements are being updated for a cohesive, professional aesthetic. Further, I\'m adjusting the muted button colors using the suggested tones for visual consistency.\n\n\n**Refining Button Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the profile selector\'s welcome message and associated buttons in `StudentCoach.tsx`. The welcome heading is updated to a serif font and muted color; the subheading follows suit. For the profile buttons, I\'m working to enhance their visual appeal, and ensure seamless style transitions. I will also incorporate the suggested natural tones for a professional, consistent look.\n\n\n**Enhancing Button Design**\n\nI\'m now revising the design of the student selection buttons within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'m working to make these stand out while maintaining visual consistency with the overall design. I am adding a new hover effect and a subtle shadow, and refining the text sizing and colors to improve readability and visual hierarchy. I am focused on creating a seamless and engaging user experience for student selection.\n\n\n**Updating Button Visuals**\n\nI\'m now implementing the latest design for the student selection buttons in `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve added a hover state that changes the border color to a darker shade. I\'m also ensuring a consistent shadow, adjusting the rounded corners, and refining transitions for a polished feel. The text size and color are also being tweaked for improved readability. The new profile button now has new bg/hover colors.\n\n\n**Styling New Profile Form**\n\nI\'m now styling the form for creating new profiles within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve applied a white background, rounded corners, a subtle border, and a shadow to it. The form will also have a header with specific text styling. I am also working on the input field styles and label to improve usability. I\'m focusing on making the form clear and easy to navigate for the user.\n\n\n**Refining Avatar Selection**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the avatar selection component within the new profile form of `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve implemented a series of emoji buttons for the user to choose their buddy avatar. The selected avatar gets a white background and a subtle shadow, while unselected ones are at 60% opacity with a hover effect for user engagement. The emoji buttons are now functional, improving user interaction.\n\n\n**Finalizing Form Interactions**\n\nI\'m now implementing the interaction logic for the new profile form within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I have now added the form functionality, focusing on user interactions, and the back and save buttons. I have added events to handle submission and canceling profile creation.\n\n\n**Styling New Input Fields**\n\nI\'m now styling the input field within the new profile form in `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'m integrating custom styling for the input, the label, and error messages (not shown). I\'m focusing on text color, background, and borders for a polished look. I am also working on improving usability and visual clarity, aiming for a seamless user experience.\n\n\n\n**Improving Avatar Selection**\n\nI\'m now refining the avatar selection design in `StudentCoach.tsx`, building upon the existing emoji buttons. I\'m focusing on better visual feedback for selected avatars, as well as a more seamless interaction. I\'ve adjusted the hover effect for unselected emojis and added a subtle transition to selected emojis. The goal is a more intuitive and visually appealing avatar selection.\n\n\n**Implementing Button Functionality**\n\nI\'m now implementing the interaction logic for the back and submit buttons within the new profile form of `StudentCoach.tsx`. The styling is already done. I\'ve integrated event handlers for seamless submission and cancellation. These buttons are designed using our styled design.\n\n\n**Enhancing Welcome Section**\n\nI\'m now revising the student welcome section within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve updated the avatar text, welcome message text color, and the \"Choose your super literacy challenge for today\" text. I\'m focusing on ensuring it aligns with the overall design, visual appeal, and readability for the user.\n\n\n**Refining Challenge Selection**\n\nI\'m now refining the challenge selection buttons within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'m focusing on ensuring visual consistency and an improved user experience. The color of the button has been updated. I\'ve also incorporated a subtle visual transition on hover, for improved feedback to the user. I\'m focusing on text and icon readability.\n\n\n**Improving Challenge Styles**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the challenge selection buttons within `StudentCoach.tsx` further. I\'m building on recent updates. I have fine-tuned the hover effect, emphasizing visual feedback. The hover now changes the bg color for improved user feedback. The text and icon readability are more polished than before. I\'m striving for seamless user engagement.\n\n\n**Refining Button Feedback**\n\nI\'m now revising the design of the \"Evidence Check\" button in `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve implemented a clearer visual distinction on hover, focusing on the border and background changes. This provides more intuitive feedback to the user. I\'m also ensuring the text and icon maintain readability, prioritizing seamless engagement.\n\n\n**Updating Challenge Feedback**\n\nI\'m now revising the style of the text indicating the active challenge and the corresponding explanatory text within `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve updated the styles with our natural tones, replacing the default indigo styles with a warm, subtle palette. I\'ve also incorporated font changes for improved readability and visual consistency.\n\n\n**Refining Recorder Visuals**\n\nI\'m now revising the recorder section of `StudentCoach.tsx`. I\'ve updated the background, border, and shadow for a cleaner look. I\'ve also increased the padding to enhance the visual layout. The focus is to refine the look of the waveform and mic button. The mic button is updated with new styles that align with the latest design.\n\n\n**Refining Text Area**\n\nI\'m now revising the text area within `StudentCoach.tsx`, focusing on visual improvements and usability. I have updated the label style and integrated a subtle border. The `textarea` element has been styled with a placeholder and I\'m updating other style attributes. The focus is now on ensuring it\'s clear, user-friendly, and aligns with the overall design.\n\n\n**Updating Button Interactions**\n\nI\'m now implementing the functionality for the back and submit buttons within the stage action buttons in `StudentCoach.tsx`. These are the final steps. I\'ve integrated event handlers to manage button state and functionality for seamless submission and stage transitions. I am focusing on smooth user interaction.\n\n\n**Adjusting Coach Panel**\n\nI\'m now revising the coach avatar panel in `StudentCoach.tsx`, applying updated styles. I\'m swapping the background color to white, modifying the border color to our design (#e5e1d5), and updating the shadow. I\'m updating the `Coach Voicey` text, using natural tones