    thinking: "**Updating the Interface**\n\nI\'m currently focused on visually updating the `TeacherDashboard.tsx` component. I\'m implementing the \"Natural Tones\" color palette. The container will get a light `#f8f7f2` background with a subtle `#e5e1d5` border. The header will use a serif font, with `#5a5a40` for titles and text using `#7d796b`. The Sync/Refresh button will feature a `#5a5a40` background, with a hover state change to `#4a4a34`.\n\n\n**Refining the Design Elements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the finer details. I\'m setting the text to white. I\'m envisioning white card backgrounds with an `#e5e1d5` border, and badges using corresponding natural colors for both background and text. I have specific colors mapped for the breakdown badges and the roster table, as well as new styling for customizer and diagnostics sections. I am leaning towards subtle contrast to highlight and improve legibility. I am thinking of using complementary color styles for raw and polished drafts.\n\n\n**Analyzing Replacement Strategies**\n\nI\'m now analyzing strategies for replacing `TeacherDashboard.tsx`. I\'m focusing on being surgical with the edits, avoiding a full file replacement as it\'s computationally expensive. I\'ve identified blocks I can replace, such as lines 72-147, and I\'m determining the best approach for chunking the remaining sections. I\'m leveraging `multi_edit_file` to accomplish this.\n\n\n**Evaluating the New Structure**\n\nI\'m now evaluating a new structure. I\'m focusing on incorporating the new components: the header, paragraph, and button, while integrating the existing content into a new, more modular grid structure. I am paying special attention to how to introduce and integrate these changes to achieve the desired improvements for the teacher console.\n\n\n**Implementing New Metrics**\n\nI\'m now implementing new metric cards within the dashboard. I\'ve integrated a card displaying total sessions and average engagement, utilizing appropriate icons from the library. I\'m focusing on the visual layout and ensuring the data is clearly presented within the grid structure. The metrics will be using a light background, and contrasting text colors for clarity.\n\n\n"
