  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have completed applying the **Natural Tones** design theme across the entire application, transforming both the **Student Coach Workstation** and the **Teacher Console** with earthy tones, organic warm details, and elegant typography.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Layout Transformation\n\n- **Consistent Color Palette**: Swapped the heavy indigo gradients and stark blue borders for warm organic tones:\n  - Background Canvas: Natural off-white and soft slate beige (`#f8f7f2` and `#efede4`).\n  - Active Cards & Highlights: Warm amber cream `#fff9ed`, soft yellow/gold accents `#9d7d2d`, and delicate sage-green `#f5f9f2`.\n  - Primary Accent & Typography: Forest moss green (`#5a5a40`) and soft matte charcoal text (`#2d2d2d`).\n- **Typography & Fluid Layouts**: Paired elegant serif headings with spacious sans-serif layouts to establish a calm, growth-oriented feel that is accessible for young readers.\n- **Student Coach Experience**:\n  - Restyled student profile badges, avatars, and custom badge earned indicators into cohesive clay/stone colors.\n  - Implemented the warm cream dialogue box for **Coach Voicey** with customized audio settings and micro-animated listening prompts.\n  - Formatted the active edit feedback and suggested hint palettes into beautiful, tactile natural cards.\n- **Teacher Dashboard Console**:\n  - Remodeled the live analytics grid, lesson track selects, and the class roster into the **Natural Tones** theme.\n  - Refined the live transcript comparisons (original speech vs. polished written text) with cream-toned speech bubbles and delicate sage-green success cards.\n- **Production Verification**: Confirmed standard type resolutions, verified syntax linting passes, and achieved a green production build pipeline."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
