  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Formulating the Summary**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the build process completed successfully without any issues. Now, I\'m focusing on crafting the final response. My primary objective is to develop a concise, professional summary that accurately explains the newly generated files and provides clear, detailed instructions for the user on how to sync them.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully created and configured all the necessary files to make your project repository fully optimized, documented, and ready for GitHub integration! Here is an overview of what has been implemented:\n\n### \360\237\223\246 GitHub Repository Assets Created\n\n* **`README.md` (Repository Documentation):** \n  * Features a beautifully structured overview of the **Literacy Lab (Voice2Literacy)** system.\n  * Documents the dynamic **COPS Scaffolding Engine** and the real-time **Teacher Console**.\n  * Contains a comprehensive directory map, detailed setup guide, installation instructions, environment configuration details, and run/build command tables.\n* **`.github/workflows/node.js.yml` (CI Workflow):** \n  * A continuous integration workflow designed to run automated builds and TypeScript checks on your repository. It tests your codebase against Node versions `18.x`, `20.x`, and `22.x` on every push or pull request to keep your code healthy.\n* **`.github/pull_request_template.md` (Pull Request Template):** \n  * A professional PR checklist to track bug fixes, features, documentation updates, building, and linting status for future contributors.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\224\204 How to Sync Your Project to GitHub\n\nAI Studio has a built-in direct synchronization tool that automates the link to your GitHub account. Follow these simple steps:\n\n1. **Open the Settings Menu:** Look at the top right of the AI Studio Build interface (next to the Share or Deploy buttons).\n2. **Select Export:** Click on the **Export** menu and select **GitHub**.\n3. **Authorize AI Studio:** Grant permission to the AI Studio integration to write to your GitHub repositories.\n4. **Select or Create Repository:** Create a brand new repository or choose an existing one to push all the codebase files (including our newly created standard files, Express server, and React components) directly into your repository!"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 31625159
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
